File: Reserve Bank Governor Lesetja Kganyago. JOHANNESBURG - Reserve Bank governor Lesetja Kganyago will stay on as governor of the bank for the next five years. President Cyril Ramaphosa re-appointed Kganyago together with two new deputies. READ: Reserve Bank governor says main task is price stability Fundi Tshazibana and Dr Rashad Cassim will assume deputies governor positions for a period of five years each. Kganyago’s second five-year term is effective from November. Tshazibana and Cassim who both hold positions within the bank, start their five-year terms on the first of next month.